{{Notability|Events|date=July 2017}}
{{Infobox Convention | name = ConGlomeration | image = | caption = | status = Active | genre = Multi-genre | venue = Crowne Plaza Louisville | location = [[Louisville, Kentucky]] | country = United States | first = 2001 | last = 2017 | attendance = 700 | website = {{URL|http://www.conglomeration.info}} }}
'''ConGlomeration'''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.louisville.com/content/keep-calm-and-geek-|title=Keep Calm and Geek On|date=2015-02-01|work=Louisville.com|access-date=2017-09-20|language=en-US}}</ref> is an annual [[multigenre convention]] held in or around [[Louisville, Kentucky]]. ConGlomeration is an all-volunteer [[non-profit]] organization which, as part of its convention programming, conducts charitable activities on behalf of the [[American Cancer Society]] and [[Cabbage Patch Settlement House]]. With the unexpected closure of the convention's hotel in 2008, the operation of the convention was disrupted, but resumed in 2010. ConGlomeration 2018 will be held at the Crowne Plaza Hotel in Louisville on Easter weekend, March 30 to April 1, 2018.
==Activities== ConGlomeration is a broad-based fan convention,<ref>{{Citation|last=Holland Rains|title=NorseMedia Goes To: ConGolmeration 2015|date=2015-04-15|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CxEbbB_SteE|accessdate=2017-09-20}}</ref> incorporating aspects of a [[gaming convention]], [[science fiction convention]] and, in 2006, 2007 and 2008, a [[writing workshop]] run by [[Apex Magazine]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jason-sizemore.com/tag/conglomeration/|title=conglomeration {{!}} a writer's vanity|website=jason-sizemore.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-20}}</ref> A 24-hour staffed game room, a [[LARP]], tracked author programming, a [[cosplay]] masquerade competition, a dealer's room, and a genre art auction are regular components of ConGlomeration's official activities.
==Mascot== The convention mascot is a [[platypus]] that dons various disguises —- including a giant [[mecha]] robot, a homage to [[Gandalf]], and [[King Kong]]—for his appearance on the official con T-shirt, which is given to staff and volunteers.
