''' Klewer Market''' is the largest textile market in [[Solo City]], [[Indonesia]].<ref name="terasolo">{{cite web|title=Pasar Klewer, Pasar Tekstil Terbesar di Kota Solo|url=http://terasolo.com/pasar/pasar-klewer.html|accessdate=14 May 2014}}</ref> The market which located beside Keraton Surakarta is also shopping center for [[batik]] traders from Yogyakarta, Surabaya, Semarang and other cities in Java.<ref name="wm">{{cite web|title=Pasar Klewer|url=http://www.wisatamelayu.com/id/object.php?a=RGdOL1B5dS9P=&nav=geo|accessdate=14 May 2014}}</ref> This market have two floors and can accommodate 1,467 traders with a number of stalls around 2,064 units.<ref name="wm"/> Klewer market not only as a center of economy, but also a tourist destination and a symbol of Solo city.<ref name="ds">{{cite web|title=Pasar Klewer|url=http://www.disolo.com/pasar-klewer/|accessdate=14 May 2014}}</ref>
== 27 December 2014 Fire == [[File:Pasar Klewer Terbakar 01.jpg|thumb|Fire broke out at Saturday night.]] On 27 December 2014 evening, the whole market was burned down.<ref>{{id}} [http://www.rri.co.id/post/berita/128854/daerah/pasar_klewer_masih_membara_solo_darurat_bencana_kebakaran.html Pasar Klewer Masih Membara, Solo Darurat Bencana Kebakaran] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141228133925/http://www.rri.co.id/post/berita/128854/daerah/pasar_klewer_masih_membara_solo_darurat_bencana_kebakaran.html |date=2014-12-28 }} (Klewer Market still aflame, Solo on red alert) - from the Indonesian National Broadcasting Agency ([[Radio Republik Indonesia]])</ref>
