{{Infobox animanga/Header | name = Ludwig II | image = Ludwig II manga.jpg | caption = English edition of the first volume of ''Ludwig II'' as published by [[Digital Manga Publishing]] | ja_kanji = ルートヴィヒⅡ世 | ja_romaji = Rūtovihi II Sei | genre = Historical, [[Yaoi]] }} {{Infobox animanga/Print | type = manga | author = [[You Higuri]] | publisher = [[Kadokawa Shoten]] | publisher_en = {{English manga publisher|NA= [[Digital Manga Publishing]]}} | demographic = | magazine = | first = 1996 | last = 1998 | volumes = 3 }} {{Infobox animanga/Footer}}
{{nihongo|'''''Ludwig II'''''|ルートヴィヒⅡ世|Rūtovihi II Sei|lead=yes}} is a Japanese [[manga]] series written and illustrated by [[You Higuri]]. It is licensed in North America by [[Digital Manga Publishing]], which released the first volume of the manga on 10 June 2009,<ref>[http://www.junemanga.com/books/330/ Ludwig II Vol. 1 - Juné Manga<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100530112517/http://www.junemanga.com/books/330/ |date=2010-05-30 }}</ref> and the second on 23 September 2009.<ref>[http://www.junemanga.com/books/331/ Ludwig II Vol. 2 - Juné Manga<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101124102713/http://www.junemanga.com/books/331 |date=2010-11-24 }}</ref> It has been licensed in France and Germany by [[Panini Comics]].<ref>[http://www.paninicomics.fr/web/guest/productDetail?viewItem=613505 paninicomics.fr - Dettaglio Prodotto<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.paninicomics.de/?s=serie&gs_gruppe=165&t=ludwig-ii-s165.html Ludwig II als Serie bei PaniniComics.de<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> It fictionalises the story of [[Ludwig II of Bavaria]].
==Release== {{Graphic novel list/header | Language = Japanese | SecondLanguage = English |Width=70% }} {{Graphic novel list | VolumeNumber = 1 | OriginalRelDate = 13 March 1996<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/199999852640/|title=ルートヴィヒII世 第1巻|publisher=[[Kadokawa Shoten]]|accessdate=21 April 2014 | language=Japanese}}</ref> | OriginalISBN = 4-04-852640-5 | LicensedRelDate = 10 June 2009<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.digitalmanga.com/books/330/ | title=Ludwig II Vol. 1 | publisher=[[Digital Manga Publishing]] | accessdate=21 April 2014}}</ref> | LicensedISBN = 978-1-56-970053-2 | ChapterList = }} {{Graphic novel list | VolumeNumber = 2 | OriginalRelDate = 29 May 1997<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/199999852822/|title=ルートヴィヒII世 第2巻|publisher=Kadokawa Shoten|accessdate=21 April 2014 | language=Japanese}}</ref> | OriginalISBN = 4-04-852822-X | LicensedRelDate = 23 September 2009<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.digitalmanga.com/books/331/ | title=Ludwig II Vol. 2 | publisher=Digital Manga Publishing | accessdate=21 April 2014}}</ref> | LicensedISBN = 978-1-56-970054-9 | ChapterList = }} {{Graphic novel list | VolumeNumber = 3 | OriginalRelDate = 29 October 1998<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/199999853018/|title=ルートヴィヒII世 第3巻|publisher=Kadokawa Shoten|accessdate=21 April 2014 | language=Japanese}}</ref> | OriginalISBN = 4-04-853018-6 | LicensedRelDate = — | LicensedISBN = | ChapterList = }} {{Graphic novel list/footer}}
==Reception== Holly Ellingwood, writing for Active Anime, enjoyed how You Higuri brought historical facts into her story.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ellingwood |first=Holly |url=http://activeanime.com/html/2009/07/06/ludwig-ii-vol-1/ |title=Ludwig II Vol. 1 |work=activeAnime |date=July 6, 2009 |accessdate=October 3, 2011 }}</ref> Casey Brienza, writing for Graphic Novel Reporter, described ''Ludwig II'' as being "an updated ''[[Rose of Versailles]]''", due to its "bold lines, asymmetrical layouts" and European setting, describing it as being less about the history than about the personalities in that time.<ref>{{cite web | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101123094858/http://graphicnovelreporter.com/content/ludwig-ii-vol-1-review |title=Ludwig II, Vol. 1 |publisher= Graphic Novel Reporter | url=http://www.graphicnovelreporter.com/content/ludwig-ii-vol-1-review | archivedate=23 November 2010}}</ref> Katherine Dacey enjoyed Higuri's "sensual artwork — her languid character designs, sumptuous interiors, and Wagnerian imagery", but disliked the sexual torture of the king's lover, Richard Hornig.<ref>[http://mangacritic.com/?p=1274#ludwig2 Short Takes: Black Bird, The Girl Who Leapt Through Time, and Ludwig II<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Leroy Douresseaux, writing for Comic Book Bin, felt "You Higuri’s use of romantic entanglements, sex, and political machinations makes for an excellent, engaging read." and also enjoyed the artwork,<ref>[http://www.comicbookbin.com/ludwig201.html Ludwig II: Volume 1 (Yaoi)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> noting Higuri's use of toning and sparkling techniques around Ludwig to symbolise the "enchanted fantasy world he wants to inhabit".<ref>[http://www.comicbookbin.com/ludwig202.html Ludwig II.: Volume 2<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Melinda Beasi, writing for PopCultureShock, felt that the plot could have been closer to real life, but noted that the "palpable loneliness" of the real Ludwig II does not fit well into the boys love genre.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.popcultureshock.com/manga/index.php/reviews/manga-reviews/ludwig-ii-vols-1-2/ |title=Ludwig II, Vols. 1-2 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5qvhBygJK?url=http://www.popcultureshock.com/manga/index.php/reviews/manga-reviews/ludwig-ii-vols-1-2/ |archivedate=2 July 2010 |author=Beasi, Melinda |date=2 January 2010 |publisher=Pop Culture Shock |accessdate=April 21, 2014 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
