{{Infobox song contest | name = Melodifestivalen | year = 1990 | theme = | logo = | final = 9 March 1990 | presenters = [[Carin Hjulström]] | winner = "[[Som en vind]]" by [[Edin-Ådahl]] | vote = Regional juries | host = | venue = [[Rondo (Gothenburg)|Rondo]], [[Gothenburg]] | entries = | interval = | opening = }}
'''[[Melodifestivalen]] 1990''' was the contest for selection of the 30th song to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was the 29th time that this method of picking a song had been used. 1,223 songs were submitted to [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] for the competition. The final was broadcast on [[SVT2|TV2]] but not on radio. The show was watched by 5,964,000 people, the biggest recorded audience for the competition (74.1% of Sweden's 1990 population).
