The '''National Day of Remembrance for Victims of Terrorism''' is marked every year on June 23 in [[Canada]] to mark the anniversary of the bombing of [[Air India Flight 182]] off the coast of [[Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://crcvc.ca/2016/06/23/national-day-of-remembrance-for-victims-of-terrorism-2/ |title=National Day of Remembrance for Victims of Terrorism |publisher=Canadian Resource Centre for Victims of Crime |date=June 23, 2016}}</ref>

On this day, flags across Canada are flown at [[half-staff|half-mast]] to honour the victims of the bombing, as well as other acts of terrorist violence that have taken lives of Canadians.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://laws-lois.justice.gc.ca/eng/regulations/SI-2005-65/FullText.html |title=Proclamation Requesting the People of Canada to Observe June 23 of Every Year as a National Day of Remembrance for Victims of Terrorism |publisher=Laws-lois.justice.gc.ca |date= |accessdate=2012-03-19}}</ref>

