{{Infobox NRHP | name = Oneonta Theatre | nrhp_type = | image = Oneonta Theatre May 11.jpg | caption = Oneonta Theatre, May 2011 | location= 47 Chestnut St., [[Oneonta, New York]] | coordinates = {{coord|42|27|12|N|75|3|50|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = New York#USA | built = 1897 | architect = | architecture = | added = May 22, 2002 | area = less than one acre | governing_body = Private | refnum = 02000555<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2009a}}</ref> }} '''Oneonta Theatre''' is a historic [[theatre]] building located at [[Oneonta, New York|Oneonta]] in [[Otsego County, New York]]. The original structure was built about 1897 and expanded in several stages. The original three story structure was a generally rectangular block with storefronts and theater entrance on the first floor and apartments above. A theater wing projected from the rear was set at a 45-degree angle. In 1922, the theater was expanded and the entrance relocated to the center of the building. The 1922 marquee was removed in the 1970s.<ref name="nrhpinv_ny">{{cite web|url=http://www.oprhp.state.ny.us/hpimaging/hp_view.asp?GroupView=8527|title=National Register of Historic Places Registration: Oneonta Theatre|date=August 2001|accessdate=2010-01-14 |author=Kathleen LaFrank|publisher=[[New York State Office of Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation]]}} ''See also:'' {{cite web|url=http://www.oprhp.state.ny.us/hpimaging/hp_view.asp?GroupView=8528|title=Accompanying five photos}}</ref>
It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2002.<ref name="nris"/> It is located within the [[Oneonta Downtown Historic District]] established in 2003.<ref name="nrhpinv_ny2">{{cite web|url=http://www.oprhp.state.ny.us/hpimaging/hp_view.asp?GroupView=11577|title=National Register of Historic Places Registration: Oneonta Downtown Historic District|date=July 2003|accessdate=2010-02-02 |author=Kathleen LaFrank|publisher=[[New York State Office of Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation]]}}</ref>
