{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}} {{Italic title}} {{ infobox music festival | music_festival_name = Swara Samrat festival | image = [[File:Swara Samrat festival logo.jpg|170px]] | caption = | location = [[Nazrul Mancha]], Kolkata | founders = ''Shreeranjani'' | dates = 5–6 January 2013 | genre = [[Indian classical music]] | website = }} '''''Swara Samrat Festival (SSF)''''' was an [[Indian classical music]] concert which was organised at the [[Nazrul Mancha]] auditorium in the [[India]]n city of Kolkata on 5–6 January 2013 by ''Shreeranjani'', a cultural organisation headed by the Sarod maestro Pandit [[Tejendra Narayan Majumdar]]. The event was dedicated to The Immortal Duo - Swara Samrat [[Ali Akbar Khan]] and Bharat Ratna [[Ravi Shankar]] (who died on 11 December 2012).<ref name="Classical legends leave their mark">{{cite news|title=Classical legends leave their mark|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-08/music-events/36215627_1_pt-jasraj-classical-legends-pt-ravi-shankar|accessdate=9 January 2013|newspaper=The Times of India|date=8 January 2013}}</ref><ref name="Indian Stage Swara Samrat festival">{{cite web|title=Swara Samrat festival|url=http://www.indianstage.in/events/swara_samrat_festival.html|accessdate=9 January 2013}}</ref> Artistes like Pandit [[Shivkumar Sharma]], Pandit [[Birju Maharaj]], Pandit [[Hari Prasad Chaurasia]], Pandit [[Jasraj]], Ustad [[Aashish Khan]], Dr. [[Girija Devi]], Pandit [[Swapan Chaudhuri]] and Ustad [[Zakir Hussain (musician)|Zakir Hussain]] performed in this festival<!-- You can wikilink these artists-->.<ref name="Classical legends leave their mark" /> == Background == {{multiple image | footer = The festival was initially planned as an event to commemorate the 90th birth anniversary of [[Ali Akbar Khan]] (left), but, after death was [[Ravi Shankar]], the organisers decided to dedicate it to [[Ravi Shankar]] (right) too. | width = 150
| image1 = Dia7275 Ali Akbar Khan r.jpg | alt1 = Ali Akbar Khan
| image2 = Dia5275 Ravi Shankar.jpg | alt2 = Ravi Shankar }} {{Quote box |quote = Tejendra Narayan has really worked hard to put this concert together. I have heard no one came forward to help him out, which is unfortunate. But such an effort will always be remembered. |source = Aashish Khan<ref name="Annapurna Devi is heartbroken: Ustad Aashish Khan Debsharma" /> |align = right |width = 35% |fontsize = | border = 1px |quoted = 1 |salign = right |sstyle = }} The two-day-long musical extravaganza was organized by ''Shreeranjani'' music organization and led by Indian [[sarod]] maestro [[Tejendra Narayan Majumdar]].<ref name="Swara Samrat Festival- Day 1">{{cite web|title=Swara Samrat Festival- Day 1|url=http://timescity.com/kolkata/events/swara-samrat-festival-day-1/65874|publisher=Times City|accessdate=9 January 2013}}</ref> The festival was initially planned as an event to commemorate the 90th birth anniversary of [[Ali Akbar Khan]]. [[Ravi Shankar]] was informed about the event. But after the death of Ravi Shankar on 11 December 2012 the organisers decided to dedicate this program to the ''[[Sitar]]'' maestro too.<ref name="Classical legends leave their mark" /><ref name="Indian Stage Swara Samrat festival" /><ref name="Two masters and a tribute">{{cite news|title=Two masters and a tribute|url=http://lite.epaper.timesofindia.com/getpage.aspx?articles=yes&pageid=27&max=true&articleid=Ar02700&sectid=11edid=&edlabel=TOICH&mydateHid=19-12-2012&pubname=Times+of+India+-+Chennai+-+Chennai+Times&title=Two+masters+and+a+tribute&edname=&publabel=TOI|accessdate=9 January 2013|newspaper=The Times of India}}</ref> Majumdar called this festival a dedication to "The Immortal Duo – Swara Samrat [[Ali Akbar Khan]] and ''[[Bharat Ratna]]'' [[Ravi Shankar]]."<ref name=Shreeranjani>{{cite web|title=Shreeranjani|url=http://www.tejendranarayan.com/?page_id=21|publisher=Tejendra Narayan Majumdar|accessdate=9 January 2013}}</ref>
In an interview, Indian ''sarod'' player [[Aashish Khan]], (who was also a performer in this event) told that Tejendra Narayan Majumdar worked very hard to organise this musical festival and found it unfortunate that no one came forward to help Tejendra Narayan.<ref name="Annapurna Devi is heartbroken: Ustad Aashish Khan Debsharma">{{cite news|title=Annapurna Devi is heartbroken: Ustad Aashish Khan Debsharma|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-05/news-and-interviews/36161030_1_classical-music-annapurna-devi-talim|accessdate=9 January 2013|newspaper=The Times of India|date=5 January 2013}}</ref>
== Performances ==
Some of most prominent classical musicians of India performed in this musical extravaganza.<ref name="Indian Stage Swara Samrat festival" /> ; On 5 January 2013 [[Shivkumar Sharma]] (Santoor) performed with Anindo Chatterjee (Tabla), [[Birju Maharaj]] ([[Kathak]]) performed with Subhankar Banerjee (Tabla), [[Hari Prasad Chaurasia]] performed with Subhankar Banerjee (Tabla), Jasraj (vocal) performed with Ramkumar Mishra (Tabla).<ref name="Indian Stage Swara Samrat festival" /><ref name="Two masters and a tribute" /><ref name="Event information at Anandabazar Parika (Bengali newspaper)">{{cite web|title=Event information at Anandabazar Parika (Bengali newspaper)|url=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ShgnBB_n9nM/UO3i07KT7xI/AAAAAAAAIaI/nCjiURTXvFE/s768/Swara+Samrat+ABP+Advertisement.jpg|publisher=Anandabazar Patrika|accessdate=9 January 2013}}</ref>
; On 6 January 2013 [[Aashish Khan]] played [[Sarod]] with Swapan Chaudhuri (Tabla). [[Girija Devi]] (vocal) performed with Samar Saha (Tabla) and [[Zakir Hussain (musician)|Zakir Hussain]] (Tabla solo) performed with Dilshad Khan (Sarangi).<ref name="Indian Stage Swara Samrat festival" /><ref name="Two masters and a tribute" /><ref name="Event information at Anandabazar Parika (Bengali newspaper)" /> ==See also== {{Portal|Indian classical music}}
